/* Write a program that prompts the user to enter three integer values, and
then outputs the values in numerical sequence separated by commas. So,
if the user enters the values 10 4 6, the output should be 4, 6, 10. If two
values are the same, they should just be ordered together. So, the input 4
5 4 should give 4, 4, 5.



I am aware that there are far more combinations than what I shared above, and that
there is a better way to write this program; with that said, I wanted to try and
solve this with the tools that were shown in the chapter
*/


#include <iostream>
int main() {
    int one{}; 
    int two{};
    int three{};

    std::cout << "Please enter three integer values: " << std::endl;
    std::cin >> one >> two >> three;

    
    if (one > two) {
        int temp = one;
        one = two;
        two = temp;
    }
    if (two > three) {
        int temp = two;
        two = three;
        three = temp;
    }
    if (one > two) {
        int temp = one;
        one = two;
        two = temp;
    }

    std::cout << one << ", " << two << ", " << three << std::endl;

    return 0;
}
